.%20With%20just%20a%20few%20private%20owners%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20no%20hiding%20or%20escaping.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ad61318d-78a5-4133-a442-12a1c34ba151%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELeaving%20on%20a%20high%20note%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEA%20is%20exiting%20the%20stock%20market%20on%20a%20high%20note.%20The%20company's%20shares%20have%20rallied%20in%20recent%20months%20in%20anticipation%20of%20%26quot%3BBattlefield%206%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20next%20installment%20of%20its%20shooter%20franchise%20due%20out%20October%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20game%20was%20expected%20to%20compete%20with%20%26quot%3BGrand%20Theft%20Auto%20VI%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20in%20May%2C%20the%20developer%20of%20that%20highly%20anticipated%20title%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftake-two-ceo-ai-better-paying-video-game-jobs-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETake-Two%20Interactive%20Software%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20postponed%20its%20release%20from%20what%20would've%20also%20been%20this%20fall%20to%20May%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20here%2C%20the%20only%20direction%20EA%20can%20likely%20go%20in%20as%20a%20publicly%20traded%20company%20%26quot%3Bis%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20Joost%20van%20Dreunen%2C%20who%20teaches%20the%20business%20of%20video%20games%20at%20New%20York%20University%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%20is%20that%20%26quot%3BBattlefield%206%26quot%3B%20will%20still%20face%20competition%20from%20Activision's%20next%20%26quot%3BCall%20of%20Duty%26quot%3B%20this%20fall%2C%20and%20eventually%20from%20%26quot%3BGrand%20Theft%20Auto%206%2C%26quot%3B%20too%2C%20which%20analysts%20expect%20to%20be%20a%20massive%20hit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20is%20that%20EA%20has%20become%20too%20dependent%20on%20dated%2C%20evergreen%20franchises%20like%20%26quot%3BThe%20Sims%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BMadden%20NFL%26quot%3B%20under%20Wilson's%20tenure%20to%20drive%20meaningful%20growth%2C%20said%20Pachter.%20He%20added%20that%20EA%20has%20also%20struggled%20to%20succeed%20in%20mobile%20gaming%2C%20the%20largest%20segment%20of%20the%20video-game%20industry%20by%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEA%20has%20tried%20a%20bunch%20of%20things%20that%20they%20believed%20would%20be%20innovative%20since%20Andrew%20became%20CEO%2C%20and%20almost%20none%20of%20them%20worked%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20going%20private%2C%20Wilson%2C%2051%2C%20can%20perhaps%20focus%20more%20on%20driving%20innovation%20at%20EA%20by%20leaning%20into%20generative%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20remarkable%20technology%20is%20not%20merely%20a%20buzzword%20for%20us.%20It's%20the%20very%20core%20of%20our%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20at%20the%20company's%20Investor%20Day%20in%20September%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilson%20could%20also%20work%20with%20the%20Saudis%20to%20expand%20EA's%20footprint%20in%20esports.%20The%20annual%20Esports%20World%20Cup%2C%20run%20by%20a%20nonprofit%2C%20is%20held%20in%20Riyadh.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20memo%20to%20employees%2C%20Wilson%20noted%20that%20he's%20excited%20to%20continue%20as%20CEO%20and%20described%20the%20deal%20as%20a%20recognition%20of%20their%20collective%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20historic%20moment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BWith%20the%20support%20of%20our%20new%20partners%2C%20the%20future%20we%20are%20building%20together%20is%20brighter%20than%20ever.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feas-ceo-andrew-wilson-relief-from-investors-55-billion-deal-2025-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1759181448000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68daf5b0cc993f9955cf2591%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feas-ceo-andrew-wilson-relief-from-investors-55-billion-deal-2025-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Andrew%20Wilson%20has%20helmed%20the%20vid